(1) East 48th Street, east side, north of Tilden Ave. A view of a frame home belonging to Cornelius Suydam of an old Brooklyn Family. (On the west, the estate was bounded by the Holy Cross Cemetery; on the east, by Utica Ave., north by Snyder Ave., and south by the old Canarsie Lane.) The home was still standing in 1929.

March 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same, another view.
1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same as view No. 1. March 1923. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3) The same, showing south and front view of house. March 1923. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(4) The same, a closer view. April 1929. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
